content.description: Start with your feet on the small outcropping and work left. The crux is a big left hand move to get to the slopey shelf. From the shelf, cut back to the right to finish just below the overhang. If you fall, be sure to push off so that you avoid hitting rock below you.
content.location: Look for the small rock outcropping just above the water that's used as the first foot placement. If you're looking at the cliff face, it's just to the right of the popular cliff jumping spot.

content.description: Rock is sharp. You'll need to tape up. Climbs are next to a cliff jumping spot, so look out for jumpers and boats. The rock is dirty and could use a good scrub. If you have a brush I'd bring it.
